                <div class="section-media-wall--list_description_origin_text nsa-accesstive">
                  <div class="nsa-accesstive" data-line="true" data-line-index="0" data-zone-id="0">
                    We have a 6 acre property in Florida that has thick, sharp, grass that grows really quick. We
                    received our Yarbo mower unit in January and have spent weekends prepping our first 1.5 acre field.
                    Clearing, raking thatch, and doing the necessary pre-cut. Now we mow this area twice per week.
                  </div>
                  <div class="nsa-accesstive" data-line="true" data-line-index="1" data-zone-id="0">
                    I’m obviously very excited about the new Yarbo Mower Pro for many reasons. The mulcher blades would
                    be a game changer for this thick St. Augustine style grass. The additional power would also help
                    make precision cuts and power through any challenges this grass has to offer.
                  </div>
